  "concept": "vuejs/core#2531: Transition component does not work with “visibility”",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:28:08.999030+00:00",
  "text": "Transition component does not work with “visibility”\n\n### Version\r\n3.0.2\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[https://codesandbox.io/s/competent-hermann-b1s5q](https://codesandbox.io/s/competent-hermann-b1s5q)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nsee https://codesandbox.io/s/competent-hermann-b1s5q\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nThe `transition` element of vue only works with `display:none` but not `visibility:hidden`.\r\nIs there any way to make it work with `visibility`? \r\nI want to get the `clientWidth` of the element before it shows up, with `display:none` I can't get that value.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
